<i>with living expenses for the time being.</i>

45
00:03:56.402 --> 00:03:59.072 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>But it’s actually a lot more fun</i>
<i>than I expected.</i>

46
00:03:59.155 --> 00:04:01.908 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>Anything involving food</i>
<i>would seem fun to you, Hachiko.</i>

47
00:04:02.825 --> 00:04:05.620 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
N-- No way! That’s not why.

48
00:04:06.371 --> 00:04:08.539 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
How should I put it…
the interaction with the customers…

49
00:04:09.874 --> 00:04:11.668 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Hey, Nobu, about this part…
-Listen to me!

50
00:04:11.751 --> 00:04:13.086 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What is it?

51
00:04:13.670 --> 00:04:18.007 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I’m convinced that working in sales
really suits me.

52
00:04:18.925 --> 00:04:21.177 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
For instance, I’m really good at that
"free smile" deal.

53
00:04:21.261 --> 00:04:24.806 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Then you should find a job
at a fast food joint.

54
00:04:24.889 --> 00:04:27.308 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
If the uniform’s cute, then I’d love that.

55
00:04:27.392 --> 00:04:28.518 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
This latest gig from the beer company

56
00:04:28.601 --> 00:04:30.019 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
requires me to wear
a campaign girl-type mini-skirt outfit,

57
00:04:30.103 --> 00:04:31.688 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
which I look pretty good in.

58
00:04:33.022 --> 00:04:34.315 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I would’ve loved to see that.

59
00:04:34.399 --> 00:04:36.943 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
That old pervert’s saying something.

60
00:04:42.365 --> 00:04:45.118 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
The Milky Way’s not visible.

61
00:04:47.245 --> 00:04:49.038 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I was so looking forward to seeing it.

62
00:04:51.416 --> 00:04:53.126 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Hey, Nobu!

63
00:04:53.209 --> 00:04:57.297 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
About meeting up tomorrow,
Yasu’s asking if we could meet there.

64
00:04:57.922 --> 00:05:01.843 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Sure! Since I’ll get off work just in time
for the opening anyway!

65
00:05:01.926 --> 00:05:02.802 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Tomorrow…</i>

66
00:05:04.387 --> 00:05:06.097 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>July 8th?</i>

67
00:05:06.931 --> 00:05:09.183 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
He says it’s okay!

68
00:05:09.267 --> 00:05:12.687 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
That’s right. Tomorrow is
Trapnest’s last performance.

69
00:05:12.770 --> 00:05:15.064 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-The three of you are going, right?
-Mm-hmm.

70
00:05:15.773 --> 00:05:18.776 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Those VIP seats.
Are they in a special section?

71
00:05:18.860 --> 00:05:21.529 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Not really. They’re center seats
on the second floor balcony.

72
00:05:21.612 --> 00:05:23.948 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I hear you get a great view,

73
00:05:24.032 --> 00:05:25.283 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
but since you’re surrounded by those
associated with the band

74
00:05:25.366 --> 00:05:27.035 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
and journalists,
the section is pretty much dead.

75
00:05:27.118 --> 00:05:29.787 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What? That sounds so boring.

76
00:05:30.788 --> 00:05:33.499 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
But we’re not exactly fans,

77
00:05:33.583 --> 00:05:36.169 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
so I’m rather thankful that I won’t
be sitting between screaming voices.

78
00:05:36.252 --> 00:05:38.921 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You should’ve had Ren
get you a seat too, Hachi.

79
00:05:39.672 --> 00:05:41.799 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It might not be too late.

80
00:05:41.883 --> 00:05:43.718 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Why don’t I ask him?

81
00:05:43.801 --> 00:05:46.429 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
No, I already saw them back home,
so it's fine.

82
00:05:46.512 --> 00:05:49.307 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Besides, I’m a bit busy tomorrow anyway.

83
00:05:49.390 --> 00:05:51.100 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You’ve got it wrong!

84
00:05:51.184 --> 00:05:53.519 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You have to write a wish
and hang it from a bamboo branch.

85
00:05:53.603 --> 00:05:55.229 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
A wish?

86
00:05:55.313 --> 00:05:56.689 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Do you seriously not know?

87
00:05:56.773 --> 00:05:58.024 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-What?
-What’s the matter?

88
00:05:58.107 --> 00:06:01.861 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Well, Shin says he’s never seen
Tanabata decorations.

89
00:06:01.944 --> 00:06:03.946 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Can you believe it? He just asked me,
"What is a tanzaku?"

90
00:06:04.030 --> 00:06:06.282 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Like I asked before, what kind of life
have you been living?

91
00:06:06.365 --> 00:06:08.409 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Didn’t you do that kind of stuff
in kindergarten?

92
00:06:08.493 --> 00:06:10.787 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I wanna write a wish on a tanzaku too.

93
00:06:10.870 --> 00:06:12.413 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Then wanna come over to write some?

94
00:06:12.497 --> 00:06:14.165 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
We still have some tanzaku left.

95
00:06:14.248 --> 00:06:15.458 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
All right!

96
00:06:20.838 --> 00:06:22.715 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
She made Tanabata decorations?

97
00:06:22.799 --> 00:06:25.426 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I told her not to, since it’s
embarrassing at her age, but…

98
00:06:30.515 --> 00:06:32.391 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
&lrm;Just a sec…

99
00:06:33.017 --> 00:06:34.602 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
All right.

100
00:06:34.685 --> 00:06:36.938 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
<i>Defeat Trapnest?</i>

101
00:06:37.021 --> 00:06:40.900 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Nobu, that’s not a wish!
That’s a resolution!

102
00:06:40.983 --> 00:06:42.360 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Yeah, I guess.

103
00:06:43.027 --> 00:06:49.075 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I’ll write a wish for Nobu.
"I want to become taller. Nobu."

104
00:06:49.158 --> 00:06:50.118 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
None of your business!

105
00:06:50.201 --> 00:06:52.495 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Besides, you’re shorter than me!

106
00:06:52.578 --> 00:06:54.247 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
But I’m still growing.

107
00:06:54.330 --> 00:06:56.499 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Sorry to say this,
but I’ll surpass your height in no time.

108
00:06:56.582 --> 00:06:58.876 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I think I’ll wish for that.

109
00:06:58.960 --> 00:07:01.129 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I wish that we can get an air conditioner.

110
00:07:01.212 --> 00:07:03.798 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I wish that I get back the car I sold.

111
00:07:03.881 --> 00:07:06.217 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I want a veranda
where I can decorate bamboo branches.

112
00:07:06.300 --> 00:07:08.177 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I want money.

113
00:07:08.261 --> 00:07:11.472 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You guys, can’t you write down
some real dreams?

114
00:07:11.556 --> 00:07:13.641 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
But this room is so damn hot!

115
00:07:13.724 --> 00:07:14.684 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Indeed.

116
00:07:14.767 --> 00:07:16.853 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
My dreams will wither in this heat.

117
00:07:17.520 --> 00:07:20.440 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Nana! The tanzakus are being blown away.

118
00:07:39.041 --> 00:07:44.380 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>That day, the clear skies of Tokyo</i>
<i>filled up with clouds in the evening,</i>

119
00:07:45.089 --> 00:07:47.592 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>and we never got to see the Milky Way.</i>

120
00:07:48.342 --> 00:07:51.762 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>However, we ended up staying up</i>
<i>all night chatting.</i>

121
00:07:58.936 --> 00:08:04.108 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>I already knew that wishing alone</i>
<i>won’t make dreams come true,</i>

122
00:08:04.192 --> 00:08:06.110 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>but I did feel that each time</i>
<i>a dream came true,</i>

123
00:08:06.194 --> 00:08:08.654 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>I would become that much happier.</i>

124
00:08:08.738 --> 00:08:10.531 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
MAY HACHIKO FIND A BOYFRIEND
(LONG-HAIRED) NANA

125
00:08:11.282 --> 00:08:14.368 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>Today, we will once again bring you</i>
<i>a wide range of special melodies,</i>

126
00:08:14.452 --> 00:08:16.162 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>from the latest hit songs</i>
<i>to nostalgic songs from the past.</i>

127
00:08:16.913 --> 00:08:18.748 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>We will kick off with a video clip</i>
<i>of a group who will be performing</i>

128
00:08:18.831 --> 00:08:23.211 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>the finale to their first nationwide tour</i>
<i>tonight. Trapnest.</i>

129
00:08:32.595 --> 00:08:33.804 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Once the tour is over…</i>

130
00:08:35.097 --> 00:08:37.225 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>I’ll come to see you.</i>

131
00:08:37.308 --> 00:08:39.810 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>When I do, would you mind</i>
<i>cooking for me again?</i>

132
00:08:47.109 --> 00:08:49.820 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>He will come. He won’t come.</i>

133
00:08:49.904 --> 00:08:52.698 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
He will come. He won’t come.

134
00:08:52.782 --> 00:08:53.616 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
He will come.

135
00:08:54.867 --> 00:08:56.118 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
He won’t come.

136
00:08:57.745 --> 00:09:01.082 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>Oh, no! Nobody in today’s age uses</i>
<i>flowers to make predictions anymore!</i>

137
00:09:01.165 --> 00:09:02.750 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>I may be insane!</i>

138
00:09:03.501 --> 00:09:05.753 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>I shouldn’t have to use flowers!</i>
<i>I know the answer!</i>

139
00:09:05.836 --> 00:09:06.921 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>There’s no way he’s coming.</i>

140
00:09:07.004 --> 00:09:11.133 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>He didn’t even reply to my email.</i>
<i>He’s probably forgotten all about me.</i>

141
00:09:12.385 --> 00:09:14.345 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>But just in case…</i>

142
00:09:15.096 --> 00:09:18.349 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>Even if Takumi doesn’t come,</i>
<i>I’m sure Ren will come.</i>

143
00:09:18.432 --> 00:09:22.228 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>There’s no big difference in cooking</i>
<i>for three people or four people.</i>

144
00:09:25.940 --> 00:09:27.149 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>I don’t know what time they’ll show up,</i>

145
00:09:27.233 --> 00:09:29.652 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>so it has to be food that’s tasty</i>
<i>even after it’s cooled.</i>

146
00:09:33.239 --> 00:09:34.865 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>These tomatoes are really delicious.</i>

147
00:09:34.949 --> 00:09:36.826 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Where did you get them from?

148
00:09:41.914 --> 00:09:45.167 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
This many veggies? Thank you, Jun-chan.

149
00:09:45.251 --> 00:09:47.712 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
The two of us can’t eat all this.

150
00:09:47.795 --> 00:09:49.380 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
They just arrived,
so they’re really fresh.

151
00:09:49.463 --> 00:09:50.298 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Today's my lucky day!

152
00:09:51.716 --> 00:09:53.843 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Well then, thank you so much, Jun-chan.

153
00:09:53.926 --> 00:09:55.511 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Come by again.

154
00:09:55.595 --> 00:09:57.972 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Kyosuke said he’d love to see you.
-Mm-hmm.

155
00:09:58.055 --> 00:10:01.684 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
But look at all the stuff you bought.
Are you expecting someone?

156
00:10:01.767 --> 00:10:04.061 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
N-- Not really. N-- No one’s coming.

157
00:10:07.940 --> 00:10:12.028 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>It’s probably for the best</i>
<i>for him not to come.</i>

158
00:10:12.111 --> 00:10:14.614 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Then I can easily give up on him.</i>

159
00:10:15.740 --> 00:10:18.659 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Besides, if Takumi comes over,</i>

160
00:10:18.743 --> 00:10:21.454 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>I will have to explain everything to Nana.</i>

161
00:10:22.079 --> 00:10:23.664 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>There’s no way I could hide</i>
<i>things any longer.</i>

162
00:10:24.874 --> 00:10:29.211 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>But if that happens, there’d</i>
<i>no longer be a reason to hide things.</i>

163
00:10:31.380 --> 00:10:35.843 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>If Takumi is the kind of guy who would</i>
<i>come to see me as he promised,</i>

164
00:10:35.926 --> 00:10:39.430 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>I would feel less guilty</i>
<i>about the situation.</i>

165
00:10:55.321 --> 00:10:58.366 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Hey, Hachiko! Who’s gonna eat all this?

166
00:10:58.449 --> 00:11:00.326 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
There’s easily enough food
for five people!

167
00:11:00.409 --> 00:11:03.704 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I guess I got a bit carried away.

168
00:11:04.330 --> 00:11:06.582 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
But I figured he'd be hungry
after the live performance.

169
00:11:06.666 --> 00:11:08.542 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I wonder what time Ren will be here.

170
00:11:08.626 --> 00:11:12.380 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Huh? He’s coming? Did he say he is?

171
00:11:12.463 --> 00:11:18.386 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
What? I don’t know,
but I assumed he’d be coming. Isn’t he?

172
00:11:18.469 --> 00:11:22.056 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I doubt he is.
He never made any such promise.

173
00:11:24.141 --> 00:11:26.227 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Why not?
-What do you mean, why not?

174
00:11:26.310 --> 00:11:27.853 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
His tour ends today,

175
00:11:27.937 --> 00:11:30.898 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
so wouldn’t he come to see you
first thing after the concert’s over?

176
00:11:30.981 --> 00:11:32.400 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
He hasn’t seen you in a month!

177
00:11:32.483 --> 00:11:33.776 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
He will definitely come!

178
00:11:33.859 --> 00:11:36.946 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
But tonight they’re partying until late
to celebrate the end of the tour.

179
00:11:37.029 --> 00:11:39.198 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It’s not likely
he’ll be able to come here.

180
00:11:39.281 --> 00:11:41.951 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Partying until late…</i>

181
00:11:42.034 --> 00:11:43.661 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I see.

182
00:11:44.412 --> 00:11:46.497 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
But he may come after that.

183
00:11:46.580 --> 00:11:51.210 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
No. If Ren comes over and stays the night,
you’d feel obligated to be hospitable.

184
00:11:51.836 --> 00:11:53.629 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
So we decided that from now on,
whenever we wanna meet,

185
00:11:53.712 --> 00:11:56.257 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I’ll go to Ren’s place.

186
00:11:56.340 --> 00:11:59.385 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
He’s not gonna suddenly show up
late at night without my knowledge.

187
00:12:00.386 --> 00:12:03.764 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>No way. I was faintly hoping that…</i>

188
00:12:03.848 --> 00:12:06.642 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>Hoping that Ren would come to see Nana,</i>
<i>and Takumi would tag along</i>

189
00:12:06.725 --> 00:12:09.311 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>with his casual</i>
<i>"Maybe I’ll come along too" attitude.</i>

190
00:12:09.937 --> 00:12:11.355 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
H-- Hey…

191
00:12:12.231 --> 00:12:14.275 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>I don’t care even if it would be</i>
<i>a casual spur of the moment decision.</i>

192
00:12:14.358 --> 00:12:16.610 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>I just hoped he would come.</i>

193
00:12:16.694 --> 00:12:19.280 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Don’t let it get you down.

194
00:12:19.363 --> 00:12:21.782 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
If you wanna see Ren,
I’ll ask him to drop by sometime.

195
00:12:22.783 --> 00:12:25.077 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
He did say he has free time
starting tomorrow.

196
00:12:25.161 --> 00:12:28.247 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Oh, if you’d like I’ll have him
invite Takumi again, and…

197
00:12:28.330 --> 00:12:30.708 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
No, it’s all right! Don’t worry about me!

198
00:12:30.791 --> 00:12:31.625 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
B-- But…

199
00:12:34.295 --> 00:12:38.215 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Well, anyway, I don’t think
he’ll be able to come today.

200
00:12:38.299 --> 00:12:41.302 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I’m sorry, considering
all the food you prepared.

201
00:12:41.385 --> 00:12:43.554 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It’s okay. It really is.
Really, don’t worry about it.

202
00:12:43.637 --> 00:12:45.931 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I’ll just put everything in the fridge.
It’ll last a few days.

203
00:12:46.015 --> 00:12:49.518 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>What am I doing?</i>
<i>I got carried away all by myself again.</i>

204
00:12:49.602 --> 00:12:52.521 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Hey, wait! I’m hungry.

205
00:12:52.605 --> 00:12:54.815 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Do you mind if I eat what I can now?

206
00:12:55.691 --> 00:12:57.276 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Sure. Of course you can.

207
00:12:57.359 --> 00:12:59.737 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I’ll get some plates.

208
00:12:59.820 --> 00:13:01.530 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
This looks really delicious.

209
00:13:01.614 --> 00:13:05.242 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Ren doesn’t know what he’s missing,
losing out on this great feast.

210
00:13:05.868 --> 00:13:07.411 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Delicious!

211
00:13:09.413 --> 00:13:12.833 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
However, seeing the way
you’re acting, you actually wanted

212
00:13:12.917 --> 00:13:15.503 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
to go to the final concert
with everyone tonight, didn’t you?

213
00:13:16.629 --> 00:13:19.298 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I should’ve asked Ren about it.

214
00:13:19.381 --> 00:13:22.885 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I’m really bad at noticing
that sort of stuff. Sorry.

215
00:13:22.968 --> 00:13:24.553 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
That’s not true.

216
00:13:24.637 --> 00:13:27.181 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Never mind me.
I bet you wanted to go, didn’t you?

217
00:13:27.264 --> 00:13:29.934 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You can be really stubborn.

218
00:13:30.017 --> 00:13:32.269 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It’s not really about being stubborn.

219
00:13:32.353 --> 00:13:33.187 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
If I saw the performance,

220
00:13:33.270 --> 00:13:35.064 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I’d end up comparing myself
and get depressed.

221
00:13:35.147 --> 00:13:36.649 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
As shameful as that is…

222
00:13:37.858 --> 00:13:41.278 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
This is great too. Looks like
we’ll be enjoying great food for a while.

223
00:13:43.864 --> 00:13:46.325 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>I’m the one who’s lousy</i>
<i>at noticing things about others.</i>

224
00:13:47.660 --> 00:13:51.247 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>I’m sorry for forcing</i>
<i>those words out of you.</i>

225
00:13:54.375 --> 00:13:57.294 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Thank you very much!

226
00:14:08.722 --> 00:14:13.310 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Today’s performance is now over.</i>

227
00:14:13.394 --> 00:14:16.146 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>People are asked to follow</i>
<i>the guidance of the staff</i>

228
00:14:16.230 --> 00:14:18.566 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>and promptly leave the premises.</i>

229
00:14:28.909 --> 00:14:30.035 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I’m going home.

230
00:14:30.119 --> 00:14:33.706 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Huh? You’re not going?
But our pass allows us to go backstage.

231
00:14:33.789 --> 00:14:35.332 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I have work to do.

232
00:14:35.958 --> 00:14:37.793 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Never mind that. Just come for a bit.

233
00:14:37.877 --> 00:14:40.921 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Sorry. Give Ren my regards.

234
00:14:41.005 --> 00:14:42.047 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What about Reira?

235
00:14:46.218 --> 00:14:47.511 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Tell her "Good job."

236
00:14:47.595 --> 00:14:48.637 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
That’s it?

237
00:14:49.597 --> 00:14:50.431 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
TRAPNEST'S BACKSTAGE ROOM

238
00:14:50.514 --> 00:14:53.058 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Huh? Where’s Yasu? Isn’t he with you?

239
00:14:53.142 --> 00:14:56.729 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
He left, saying he had work to do.
He sends his regards to Ren.

240
00:14:56.812 --> 00:14:59.315 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Huh? What about me?
-No way!

241
00:14:59.398 --> 00:15:02.651 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I was really looking forward
to seeing him.

242
00:15:02.735 --> 00:15:04.528 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I guess it wasn’t mutual, Naoki.

243
00:15:04.612 --> 00:15:09.700 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I was also looking forward
to seeing him. So it wasn’t mutual?

244
00:15:09.783 --> 00:15:10.910 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
This is so painful.

245
00:15:10.993 --> 00:15:14.580 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Reira, you realize it’s hard to come up
with a comeback phrase in your case.

246
00:15:14.663 --> 00:15:16.457 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It wasn’t mutual? This is so painful.

247
00:15:16.540 --> 00:15:19.376 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Not to mention there are writers
around us taking notes.

248
00:15:20.002 --> 00:15:22.546 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Take, it’s not a laughing matter.

249
00:15:22.630 --> 00:15:25.591 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Yasu asked me to tell you
that you did a good job.

250
00:15:26.550 --> 00:15:29.345 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Wow, what a pretty boy!

251
00:15:29.428 --> 00:15:32.014 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Come play with me.
-Hey!

252
00:15:33.223 --> 00:15:35.517 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Sure, but I’m expensive.

253
00:15:35.601 --> 00:15:37.186 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
One hundred thousand yen per night
for the "works".

254
00:15:37.269 --> 00:15:38.103 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Shin!

255
00:15:38.187 --> 00:15:40.314 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You’re cute too. How much?

256
00:15:40.397 --> 00:15:42.566 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Ren, save me. What’s up with this person?

257
00:15:43.525 --> 00:15:45.319 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I think I'll go home.

258
00:15:45.402 --> 00:15:47.446 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Come on. We’re partying. Come join us.

259
00:15:47.529 --> 00:15:50.407 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We’ve got a second and third party
lined up, so we’ll be at it until morning.

260
00:15:50.491 --> 00:15:52.284 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Yay! I’m coming, I’m coming.

261
00:15:52.368 --> 00:15:53.494 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Yay, come, come.

262
00:15:53.577 --> 00:15:55.621 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Yeah, I’m coming, I’m coming.

263
00:16:06.048 --> 00:16:07.174 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Gin and tonic.

264
00:16:07.257 --> 00:16:10.177 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Are you sure, Nobu?
We’re only at the second party.

265
00:16:10.260 --> 00:16:11.220 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Shouldn’t you slow down with the drinking?

266
00:16:11.303 --> 00:16:14.014 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I can’t blend in with this atmosphere
unless I’m drunk.

267
00:16:14.098 --> 00:16:16.225 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Such a pure-hearted guy!

268
00:16:17.059 --> 00:16:20.688 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I wonder why Yasu went out
with such a weird woman.

269
00:16:20.771 --> 00:16:21.981 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Weird woman?

270
00:16:22.064 --> 00:16:23.732 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
The mysteries of Yasu keep building.

271
00:16:23.816 --> 00:16:26.151 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I can’t let you talk like that, Nobu.

272
00:16:26.235 --> 00:16:29.405 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
How dare you talk
about our princess like that.

273
00:16:29.488 --> 00:16:32.783 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Takumi… Sorry to bother you,
but could you please autograph these?

274
00:16:32.866 --> 00:16:36.120 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
What. What’s this? You're making me work,
even in this place?

275
00:16:36.203 --> 00:16:37.329 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Sorry.

276
00:16:37.413 --> 00:16:40.165 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I got autographs from the others
during breaks at rehearsals,

277
00:16:40.249 --> 00:16:43.210 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
but you seemed busy, so I was
gonna ask you later then forgot.

278
00:16:43.836 --> 00:16:45.838 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It’s a request
from a very important sponsor.

279
00:16:45.921 --> 00:16:48.632 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Okay, okay. If it’s so important,
then you shouldn’t forget.

280
00:16:48.716 --> 00:16:49.550 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Sorry.

281
00:16:49.633 --> 00:16:51.385 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Pull yourself together, manager.

282
00:16:52.094 --> 00:16:53.512 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
So you’re signing them? Good for you.

283
00:16:53.595 --> 00:16:54.596 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I’m a mature man after all.

284
00:16:55.264 --> 00:16:57.683 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You’re the one who does
the musical arrangements

285
00:16:57.766 --> 00:16:59.435 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
for all the Trapnest songs, right Takumi?

286
00:16:59.518 --> 00:17:00.436 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
That’s right.

287
00:17:00.519 --> 00:17:04.273 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
And you also produced
your latest album, right?

288
00:17:04.356 --> 00:17:05.190 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Well, yeah.

289
00:17:05.274 --> 00:17:08.027 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
So that’s why it’s
so much better than the first one.

290
00:17:08.110 --> 00:17:11.613 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Oh? You’re cute. How about
for two hundred thousand yen?

291
00:17:11.697 --> 00:17:13.866 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
But you’re seriously great.

292
00:17:13.949 --> 00:17:15.242 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
How do you manage to make

293
00:17:15.325 --> 00:17:18.704 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
such fancy music
out of Ren’s dark, twisted songs?

294
00:17:18.787 --> 00:17:20.956 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Excuse me for writing dark, twisted songs.

295
00:17:21.665 --> 00:17:22.499 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Shochu!

296
00:17:22.583 --> 00:17:25.794 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
But it’s all possible
because of Ren’s songs.

297
00:17:25.878 --> 00:17:27.296 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
How do you manage
to get on everyone’s good side?

298
00:17:27.379 --> 00:17:29.089 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
By the way, Takumi,

299
00:17:29.173 --> 00:17:31.216 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
could you sign an autograph for me, too?

300
00:17:31.300 --> 00:17:33.177 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Sure. But do you have autograph paper?

301
00:17:33.260 --> 00:17:35.596 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
No, I don’t. Just give me one of those.

302
00:17:35.679 --> 00:17:38.015 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
But these are for our important sponsors.

303
00:17:38.098 --> 00:17:39.141 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What do I care?

304
00:17:39.224 --> 00:17:40.601 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>He’s just like Nana.</i>

305
00:17:41.477 --> 00:17:42.561 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
To whom?

306
00:17:42.644 --> 00:17:43.771 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Hachiko.
-Huh?

307
00:17:43.854 --> 00:17:45.355 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Ren, if it’s for Hachi,

308
00:17:45.439 --> 00:17:47.649 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
why not do the favor of having him
write out her full name?

309
00:17:47.733 --> 00:17:49.526 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What is her full name?

310
00:17:50.152 --> 00:17:53.489 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Hachi… Where have I heard that before?

311
00:17:53.572 --> 00:17:55.199 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You met her a while ago, Takumi.

312
00:17:55.282 --> 00:17:58.035 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
At the mahjong tournament. Nana Komatsu.

313
00:17:58.118 --> 00:18:00.037 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Oh, yes, Nana.

314
00:18:03.791 --> 00:18:06.543 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
She may no longer want
an autograph from me.

315
00:18:06.627 --> 00:18:08.670 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Huh? But she said she wanted one.

316
00:18:08.754 --> 00:18:10.964 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-When?
-The day of the mahjong game.

317
00:18:12.299 --> 00:18:15.469 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Then there’s no need.
We did it the next day.

318
00:18:15.552 --> 00:18:17.721 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Where did Take go?

319
00:18:19.473 --> 00:18:22.684 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Wait. What do you mean, "You did it"?

320
00:18:22.768 --> 00:18:25.646 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What? You want me to explain it to you?

321
00:18:25.729 --> 00:18:27.981 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
She’s my girl’s best friend.

322
00:18:28.065 --> 00:18:30.067 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It’s one thing to fool around with women,
but you’ve gone too far.

323
00:18:30.150 --> 00:18:33.278 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Know your limits.
-Don’t get all worked up.

324
00:18:33.362 --> 00:18:37.157 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It’s not as if I forced myself onto her.
She agreed to it.

325
00:18:37.241 --> 00:18:39.743 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
She was wagging her tail
looking all pleased.

326
00:18:47.334 --> 00:18:48.460 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Hey, you!

327
00:18:48.544 --> 00:18:51.630 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Take, it’s nothing.
They’re just fooling around.

328
00:18:54.299 --> 00:18:56.343 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
If you wanna fight, let’s take it outside.

329
00:18:56.426 --> 00:18:59.638 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It’s a party for all the tour staff.
Don’t spoil it.

330
00:19:06.061 --> 00:19:07.563 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Nobu…
-I’m going home.

331
00:19:08.689 --> 00:19:09.815 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You’re going home?

332
00:19:11.859 --> 00:19:13.026 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Takumi…

333
00:19:17.239 --> 00:19:18.615 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Good job.

334
00:19:21.827 --> 00:19:23.662 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
The autographs!

335
00:19:23.745 --> 00:19:25.122 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Are you all right, Takumi?

336
00:19:26.707 --> 00:19:29.710 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Shin is so awesome!
-Don’t laugh, Reira.

337
00:19:29.793 --> 00:19:31.795 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Don’t get all upset, Takumi.
You’re the one at fault.

338
00:19:31.879 --> 00:19:34.840 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I was just telling the truth!
What’s wrong with that?

339
00:19:35.465 --> 00:19:38.552 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You think you did
absolutely nothing wrong?

340
00:19:39.428 --> 00:19:40.971 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I’m going home too.

341
00:19:41.054 --> 00:19:43.348 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You can’t leave, Takumi.
We’ve still got the third party to go to.

342
00:19:43.432 --> 00:19:44.308 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Continue without me.

343
00:19:44.391 --> 00:19:45.934 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Takumi, the autographs…

344
00:19:46.018 --> 00:19:48.353 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I’ll redo them tomorrow
and send them to you.

345
00:19:48.937 --> 00:19:50.814 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Thanks to this, I just remembered
something important that I must do.

346
00:19:50.898 --> 00:19:52.566 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What? A woman thing again?

347
00:19:52.649 --> 00:19:53.775 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
When you see Nobu, tell him that

348
00:19:54.651 --> 00:19:56.320 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
he cannot reach my level
even in a hundred years.

349
00:19:57.237 --> 00:19:59.698 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
He doesn’t have the guts
to make a woman his, so stop fussing.

350
00:20:00.866 --> 00:20:02.534 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I agree with the second half.

351
00:20:03.535 --> 00:20:04.703 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I’ll give him the message.

352
00:20:22.596 --> 00:20:25.557 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>What is it at this time of night?</i>

353
00:20:28.352 --> 00:20:29.269 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Hey, Hachi…

354
00:20:52.751 --> 00:20:54.002 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Hey, Nana…</i>

355
00:20:55.629 --> 00:20:58.966 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>Why are having a dream come true</i>
<i>and achieving happiness</i>

356
00:20:59.049 --> 00:21:01.260 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>two different things?</i>

357
00:21:02.970 --> 00:21:06.974 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
<i>I still don’t get it, even now.</i>

358
00:21:07.057 --> 00:21:08.517 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
MAY HACHIKO FIND A BOYFRIEND
(LONG-HAIRED) NANA

